issues_found.evidence:
Code (keystone_webhook.go:86-93) now only defaults Processes and Threads:
```go
if obj.Spec.UWSGI != nil {
    if obj.Spec.UWSGI.Processes == 0 {
        obj.Spec.UWSGI.Processes = 2
    }
    if obj.Spec.UWSGI.Threads == 0 {
        obj.Spec.UWSGI.Threads = 2
    }
}
```
But docs (keystone-crd.md:240-243) say:
> The defaulting webhook handles this by only setting `httpKeepAlive=true` when the **entire** struct is zero-valued (`processes==0 && threads==0 && httpKeepAlive==false`).

Test TestDefault_UWSGIZeroValuedDefaultsProcessesAndThreads confirms: `g.Expect(k.Spec.UWSGI.HTTPKeepAlive).To(BeFalse())` — the webhook does NOT set it to true.
